1537	  triple-overlap chart ring \(R_{IJK} := \mathrm{Localization.Away}\,(P^I_J\cdot P^I_K)\)
1538	  the composite ring endomorphism
1539	  \[
1540	    \Phi := \Theta_{I,J,K} \circ \mathrm{swap}_J \circ \Theta_{J,K,I} \circ \mathrm{swap}_K
1541	            \circ \Theta_{K,I,J} \circ \mathrm{swap}_I
1542	  \]
1543	  equals the identity \(\mathrm{RingHom.id}\,R_{IJK}\), where each \(\Theta_{X,Y,Z} =
1544	  \mathtt{cocycleΘIJ}\,d\,r\,X\,Y\,Z\) (\cref{def:gr_cocycle_theta_ij}, taken for the rotated index
1545	  triple) and each \(\mathrm{swap}_X\) is the matching order-swap algebra equivalence
1546	  \(\mathtt{awayMulCommEquiv}\) (\cref{def:gr_away_mul_comm_equiv}).
