1552	  \(R_{IJK} = \mathrm{Localization.Away}\,(P^I_J\cdot P^I_K)\), so by Mathlib's
1553	  \(\mathrm{IsLocalization.ringHom\_ext}\) for the submonoid generated by
1554	  \(P^I_J\cdot P^I_K\) it suffices to
1555	  check equality on the chart-ring generators (the images of the universal matrix entries). On those
1556	  generators \(\Phi\) unwinds, via the order-swaps and the \(\Theta\) definitions, to the rotated
1557	  analogue of the matrix cocycle collapse \((Y_K)^{-1}Y\) already proved in
