2064	\begin{proof}
2065	  \uses{def:gr_glued_scheme, def:gr_transition, lem:gr_diagonalRingMap_surjective, lem:gr_separated_toSpecZ}
2066	  \leanok
2067	  The products \(U^I \times_{\mathbb{Z}} U^J\), as \(I, J\) range over the
2068	  size-\(d\) subsets, form an affine open cover of \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)
2069	  \times_{\mathbb{Z}} \mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\). Separatedness may be checked on this
2070	  cover: it suffices to show that for each pair \((I,J)\) the preimage
2071	  \(\Delta^{-1}(U^I \times_{\mathbb{Z}} U^J)\) maps by a closed immersion into
2072	  \(U^I \times_{\mathbb{Z}} U^J\), i.e.\ that the corresponding ring
2073	  homomorphism is surjective.
