2096	  \(\mathbb{Z}[X^I, 1/P^I_J]\) and \(\delta_{I,J}\) is surjective. Concretely the
2097	  closed subscheme \(\Delta_{I,J} \subseteq U^I \times_{\mathbb{Z}} U^J\) is cut
2098	  out by the entries of the matrix relation
2099	  \[
2100	    X^J_I \, X^I - X^J \;=\; 0,
