2103	  \(X^J_I = (X^I_J)^{-1} X^I_I = (X^I_J)^{-1}\) and therefore \(X^J_I X^I =
2104	  (X^I_J)^{-1} X^I = X^J\). As each restricted diagonal is a closed immersion,
2105	  \(\Delta\) is a closed immersion and \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\) is separated over
2106	  \(\mathbb{Z}\).
2107	\end{proof}
